{
  "stem": "26699.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't have enough room in our small house, so we moved the piano in a block of flats, a flat of one of our relatives.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And during the bombing, the block of flats was totally demolished, and the only object which survived was the piano, to my regret because I wasn't a great piano player and fan.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Simply was left there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a store full of fabrics.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He managed to save some of them when he went with that truck and to bring them to Bucharest, some of them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there was lootings, and nothing was left.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, after this August day, the liberation day by the Red Army.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] In September, school starts again, so I was enrolled to a Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Bucharest, they had better conditions than in Iasi, so we stayed there for learning in the synagogues.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had a couple of Jewish schools, which were overcrowded, but still, they looked like schools.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I was accepted in the fourth class.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The first three I spent in Iasi, and the fourth in Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "To my amazement was that in spite of the hard conditions that we had in Iasi, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] my education in this new school when we started was colleagues who were educated in a proper school in Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My level was very similar to theirs, which showed to me for the rest of my life that not the walls are making their [? vocation, ?] but the teachers and the pupils, and of course the parents.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after four years, which was called the primary school, I went to the intermediate school, which was called a gymnasium, a different name from other places.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't the high school.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
